n Venice", "c": "John Lewis", "w": "74202"}]}, {"id": "36375", "date": "1989-02-01", "label": "Black History Makers Awards Ceremony", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Percy Heath", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Before we get from the transition from Kenny Clarke to Connie Kay, I wanna talk a couple things in those early recordings. On “One Bass Hit” and on the “La Ronde Suite,” we have the first recorded solos of Percy Heath in the Modern Jazz Quartet... Connie Kay coming in... Connie Kay, when John says, ", "doc_title": "Percy Heath — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Heath-Percy/Heath_Percy_Interview_Transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "David N. Baker", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "The drummer was Connie Kay. It was a wonderful group of musicians, and it was the same music that had comprised, first of all, The Golden Striker...", "doc_title": "David N. Baker — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/David%20N.%20Baker%20SI-NEA%20oral%20history%20%282%29.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Jim Hall", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "there were three of us that had this group—Connie Kay, the drummer from the MJQ, and Bill Evans and me.", "doc_title": "Jim Hall — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Hall-Jim/Jim-Hall_transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Derek Smith", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "And it was with Percy Heath and Connie Kay — not a bad rhythm section.", "doc_title": "Derek Smith interviewed by Monk Rowe and Michael Woods, Majesty of the Seas, May 29, 1995", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/derek-smith-interviewed-monk-rowe-and-michael-woods-majesty-seas-may-29-1995"}, {"speaker": "George Masso", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "Al Klink, Bucky Pizzarelli, John Bunch, Slam Stewart, various drummers, numerous drummers, Joe Corsello was one of them, and oh God, Mousey Alexander sometimes, and Connie Kay.", "doc_title": "George Masso interviewed by Monk Rowe, Aspen, Colorado, October 10, 1997", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/george-masso-interviewed-monk-rowe-aspen-colorado-october-10-1997"}, {"speaker": "John Pizzarelli, Jr.", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "just for good measure we get Connie Kay on the drums. It was either Connie Kay or Mel Lewis. And God bless them both. And Mel couldn't make it so we got Connie Kay.", "doc_title": "John Pizzarelli, Jr. interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, January 29, 2000 [interview 1 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/john-pizzarelli-jr-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-january-29-2000"}]}